de.mpg.biochem.mars.molecule

Class SingleMoleculeArchive

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mpg.biochem.mars.molecule.AbstractMoleculeArchive<SingleMolecule,MarsOMEMetadata,SingleMoleculeArchiveProperties>
      • de.mpg.biochem.mars.molecule.SingleMoleculeArchive
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JsonConvertibleRecord, MoleculeArchive<SingleMolecule,MarsOMEMetadata,SingleMoleculeArchiveProperties>

    public class SingleMoleculeArchive
extends AbstractMoleculeArchive<SingleMolecule,MarsOMEMetadata,SingleMoleculeArchiveProperties>
    Implementation of AbstractMoleculeArchive for default archives used for routine single molecule time-series datasets composed of SingleMolecule molecule records, MarsMetadata metadata records, and SingleMoleculeArchiveProperties archive properties.

    For a more extensive explanation of uses and features of molecule archives see AbstractMoleculeArchive.

    Author:
    Karl Duderstadt

      • SingleMoleculeArchive

        public SingleMoleculeArchive(java.io.File file)
                      throws java.io.IOException,
                             com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonParseException
        Constructor for loading a SingleMoleculeArchive. A yama file can be given or a yama virtual store directory. Virtual mode will automatically be activated if a directory is provided.

        MoleculeArchives should typically be opened using the ImportVirtualStoreCommand, which automatically detect the type and open the archive accordingly.

        Parameters:
        file - The file or directory to load the archive from.
        Throws:
        com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonParseException - if there is a problem parsing the file provided.
        java.io.IOException - if there is a problem with the file location.

      • SingleMoleculeArchive

        public SingleMoleculeArchive(java.lang.String name,
                             java.io.File file)
                      throws com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonParseException,
                             java.io.IOException
        Constructor for loading a SingleMoleculeArchive. A yama file can be given or a yama virtual store directory. Virtual mode will automatically be activated if a directory is provided. If the MoleculeArchiveService is provided the statusService will be retrieved and when working in Fiji the progress shows up in the bar as molecule records are loaded.

        MoleculeArchives should typically be opened using the ImportVirtualStoreCommand, which automatically detect the type and open the archive accordingly.

        Parameters:
        name - The name of the archive.
        file - The file or directory to load the archive from.
        Throws:
        com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonParseException - if there is a parsing exception.
        java.io.IOException - if there is a problem with the file provided.

      • SingleMoleculeArchive

        public SingleMoleculeArchive(java.lang.String name,
                             MarsTable table)
        Constructor for building a SingleMoleculeArchive from a MarsTable. The table provided must contain a molecule column. The integer values in the molecule column determine the grouping for creation of molecule records. Status will be reported during processing by retrieving the StatusService from the MoleculeArchiveService instance.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the archive.
        table - A MarsTable to build the archive from.
